        "content": "<p>For this given example </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c\">/-</span><span class=\"cm\"> A toy mouse changes speed from a constant 2 m/s to 0 m/s in the span of two seconds.</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">It's mass is estimated to be around 0.1 kg.</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">The toy can only handle two Newtons of force.</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">Prove that the force it experiences is below this limit. -/</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">toy_mouse_force_limit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">v₀</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">v₁</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h4</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h5</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">v₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v₀</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h6</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n<span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">v₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v₀</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">):=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"kd\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>used ChatGPT 4o to create Lean code based on world problem with following prompt.</p>\n<p><strong>Prompt</strong> (<a href=\"https://chatgpt.com/\">ChatGPT 4o</a>)</p>\n<p>Given the following word problem, create the Lean 4 prover code as a student exercise to be solved using single chain of expressions.</p>\n<p>Use Lean example instead of theorem or lemma.<br>\nInclude variable after keyword example in a format like example { x y : R}.<br>\nUse hypothesis in a format like (h1 : 10 = (a - b) ).<br>\nPut example, hypothesizes and conclusion on separate lines.<br>\nUse Lean sorry instead of providing solution.<br>\nUse words for variable name with underscores.<br>\nConvert each statement to one hypothesis if possible.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">toy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mouse</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">changes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">speed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">constant</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">span</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">two</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">seconds</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">It's</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mass</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">estimated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">be</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">around</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kg</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">The</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">toy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">can</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">handle</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">two</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Newtons</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">force</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Prove</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">that</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">it</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">experiences</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">below</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">limit</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>Reply</strong> </p>\n<p>Here's the Lean 4 prover code for the given word problem:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">speed_initial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">speed_final</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">time_span</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mass</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">max_force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">speed_initial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">speed_final</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">time_span</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mass</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">max_force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">max_force</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This sets up the problem with the given hypotheses and leaves the proof as an exercise to be solved.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Being a programmer and not a mathematician don't really know what to think of the differences, thus looking for insight. Thanks</p>",
